The paper discusses indexing databases for similarity search, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). The asymptotic analysis and cost model used in the paper suggest that it may also be relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
